stories.text: I am working in tech and reading a lot of entepreneur books and articles. I have a hard time getting my head around the fact that I am spending all my time at work only to get a fixed salary. I mean, if i have been owning a slice of my employee it would have felt better to give that 110% instead of 100%. At the same time I thrive the most when doing that little extra. Anyone else feeling the same? How do you cope with that?
